  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `erigon version 2022.99.99-dev-0d08bd09`\r\n\r\nCommit hash : 0d08bd096fb78a8ba4a1788583eb011ac488c1fc\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nNo internal desc runtime errors. I can send eth_sendRawTransaction fine.\r\n```\r\n$ sudo ./rpcdaemon --datadir=dev --private.api.addr=localhost:9091 --http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool,parity --http.port 8545\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.244] DB schemas compatible                    reader=6.0.0 database=6.0.0\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.285] [Snapshots] see new                      blocks=0\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.285] rpc filters: subscribing to Erigon events \r\nTraceRequests = false\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.288] HTTP endpoint opened                     url=localhost:8545 ws=false ws.compression=false grpc=false\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.293] interfaces compatible                    remote_db= client=6.0.0 server=6.0.0\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.293] interfaces compatible                    remote_service=eth_backend client=3.1.0 server=3.1.0\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.293] interfaces compatible                    remote_service=mining client=1.0.0 server=1.0.0\r\nINFO[08-08|12:54:14.294] interfaces compatible                    remote_service=tx_pool client=1.0.0 server=1.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\n$ ./rpcdaemon --datadir=dev --private.api.addr=localhost:9091 --http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool,parity --http.port 8545\r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:14.252] DB schemas compatible                    reader=6.0.0 database=6.0.0\r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:14.275] rpc filters: subscribing to Erigon events \r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:14.278] HTTP endpoint opened                     url=localhost:8545 ws=false ws.compression=false grpc=false\r\nWARN[08-09|14:14:55.321] [Snapshots] reopen                       err=\"rpc error: code = Internal desc = runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\"\r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:55.322] interfaces compatible                    remote_db= client=6.0.0 server=6.0.0\r\nWARN[08-09|14:14:55.322] [Snapshots] reopen                       err=\"rpc error: code = Internal desc = runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\"\r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:55.322] interfaces compatible                    remote_service=eth_backend client=3.1.0 server=3.1.0\r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:55.322] interfaces compatible                    remote_service=mining client=1.0.0 server=1.0.0\r\nINFO[08-09|14:14:55.323] interfaces compatible                    remote_service=tx_pool client=1.0.0 server=1.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nIssue originally noticed when sending eth_sendRawTransaction on dev chain (see response below), so expected result would be also the transaction succeeded:\r\n1) Pull latest `devel` changes\r\n2) Build erigon and rpcdaemon ( `make erigon && make rpcdaemon` )  \r\n3) Start erigon and start rpcdaemon: `./erigon --datadir=dev --chain dev --private.api.addr=localhost:9091 --mine --http=false --http.port=8545`\r\n`./rpcdaemon --datadir=dev --private.api.addr=localhost:9091 --http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool,parity --http.port 8545`\r\n(Actual result of stacktrace of RPCdaemon visible above)\r\n4) Try to send transaction: \r\n```\r\ncurl --location --request POST 'localhost:8545' \\\r\n--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n--data-raw '{\"jsonrpc\":2.0,\"method\":\"eth_sendRawTransaction\", \"params\": [\"0xf86c80843b9aca0082520894a94f5374fce5edbc8e2a8697c15331677e6ebf0b87470de4df82000080820a96a054533dba7ea5edabe2c875baf70bef36352a82786e5d826781265a426dea78cea04348961fa435012b76a14dbf6228c13a2475d3243dd3fcc8c373f4defa6b8ad2\"],\r\n     \"id\": 12}'\r\n```\r\n \r\n**Actual result:**\r\n```\r\n\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"id\": 12,\r\n    \"error\": {\r\n        \"code\": -32000,\r\n        \"message\": \"method handler crashed\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
